Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A man was arrested on Wednesday for allegedly printing counterfeit money in his home in Montclair, Durban, KwaZulu-Natal police said.The 44-year-old was caught in the early hours of Wednesday morning during an operation involving police and the Durban Hawks, spokesperson for the Ethekwini Inner police cluster, Priya Nunkumar said.Counterfeit money with an estimated value of R500 000 was confiscated, along with two printers and ink. Cluster commander, Major General Keerath Nunkumar, cautioned businesses and members of the public to be cautious when accepting money.&nbsp;&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.